[run_task_loop] Claimed task: task-01 — Add a --tui flag to inspect_layout.js that launches an interactive terminal UI showing a spatial wireframe of the layout — a visual map of the page rendered in the terminal, not a JSON tree. The layout JSON already contains pixel coordinates (rect.x, rect.y, rect.width, rect.height) and colors for every node. Scale these coordinates to fit the terminal window size (use process.stdout.columns / process.stdout.rows), then draw each layout region as a labeled box at its proportional position using ANSI escape codes or a terminal canvas library. Regions that overlap should render child regions on top of parent regions (paint in tree order: root first, children after). Each box should show its label text (node.label) and ideally its background color as an ANSI 256-color or truecolor background fill. Use the 'blessed' npm library installed into the skill's own node_modules at /workspaces/skills/layout-inspecting/scripts/node_modules/ via npm install --prefix /workspaces/skills/layout-inspecting/scripts blessed. The existing self-install bootstrap (lines 38-83 of inspect_layout.js) should be extended to auto-install blessed. Press 'q' to quit. The TUI renders the already-computed layout JSON in memory — no second browser fetch. --tui is incompatible with --output (print an error if both are given).
